items.title: Apple supplier Jabil plans Rs 2,000-cr electronics manufacturing plant in Trichy
items.description: The supplier to Apple, Cisco and HP inked a memorandum of understanding (MoU) with the firm's officials on September 10 in the presence of chief minister M K Stalin, who is currently on a tour of the US

items.title: Morning Scan: All the big stories to get you started for the day
items.description: Start your day ahead of the curve with our sharp, curated morning news roundup. Get the key stories from top newspapers and stay informed about the most important developments across various sectors

items.title: Oracle beats quarterly estimates as demand for its cloud services rises
items.description: The Texas-based company's push into the cloud computing market is showing promising results and it has started narrowing the gap with market leaders Microsoft and Amazon Web Services.

items.title: UBS weighs wealth tie-up to compete in cutthroat Indian market
items.description: The Swiss bank has held early-stage internal discussions about possibilities including buying a stake in a local firm to form a joint venture, the people said, asking not to be named discussing private information
